    "translation":{"eng":"I have not accepted the tenets of religiosity; rather, my conscious­ness has been absorbed in irreligious matters. I have not aspired for your lotus feet. Narottama dāsa says, “O Vaiṣṇava Ṭhākura, I fear what I see and hear around me. Grant me deliverance and keep me near you.”"}}
